        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 3:20PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cotton Valley, or 10 miles northwest of Minden, moving west at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cotton Valley, Sarepta, Ivan, and Couchwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
